{
  "texts": [
    "The interaction between the environment and the agent is illustrated in Figure 5.",
    "The RL objective function can be formulated as max π E[ ∞ ℓ=0 γ ℓ r ℓ], where γ ∈ [0, 1] refers to the discount factor.",
    "The importance of the future reward increases with γ.",
    "For example, if γ = 0, the agent focuses only on maximizing the current instantaneous reward.",
    "On the other hand, if γ = 1, it aims to maximize the long-term cumulative reward."
  ]
}